<br>
No, my point is the new Luclin armor and models.<br>
<br>
Now that the novelty has worn off, I'm really starting to hate them, or at least most of them.<br>
<br>
Let's take the first shining example, the poor half-elf males. In the old days, they were among the coolest-looking plate wearers. Now they look like bandy-legged football players while in plate, and the pieces look mismatched even when they're not. Did different people design each piece? Their crafted armor pieces are different shades of blue. Their boots have a strange chunky, striped look, directly contrasting with the detail on the greaves, which, by the way, are totally matte and do not have a plate appearance at all, much like most of the rest of their armor. Did they forget that metal looks shiny? I know that half-elves are not the only race whose plate armor has zero reflective quality.  Humans are looking pretty matte too. <br>
<br>
Why do half-elven males only have three hairstyles, and no &quot;long&quot; style at all? <br>
<br>
Why do they kick like a girl?<br>
<br>
Why does a leather tunic look *virtually identical* to wearing *nothing* on a half-elf male? <br>
<br>
<br>
Other annoyances:<br>
<br>
Why does my High Elf female have to wear an ugly banded tunic under her plate breastplate? Why do her plate boots show through the sides of a banded skirt?<br>
<br>
Why does almost everyone look the same in a leather-based helm?<br>
<br>
Why did they not take long hair/ponytails into account when designing the high-collared caster robes?<br>
<br>
Why do so many races have to look so damned hunchbacked all the time, greatly exacerbated if wearing a plate breastplate? A High Elf woman should be straight-backed even if she's had a long, hard day. I don't hunch my shoulders over when I turn around in real life; do you?<br>
<br>
Do Barbarian males really like the way they look now? All bow-legged? Come to that, why did so many races lose so much of their prior nobility? <br>
<br>
Why does chain-based armor look so fussy and cluttered and *ugly* on so many races? <br>
<br>
*sigh*<br>
<br>
I much preferred the new Velious textures. I think I would have preferred more armors like that instead of Verant's obviously rushed, aesthetically mediocre attempt at making armor that has it's own geometry. <br>
<br>
The good artists must have quit.<br>
